WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-PT

00:00:00.066 --> 00:00:02.950
Runic forms, inscriptions.

00:00:02.950 --> 00:00:05.800
This is my life's work.

00:00:05.800 --> 00:00:08.350
The more I studied,
the more I began to see

00:00:08.350 --> 00:00:11.350
similar shapes in the stars in the sky.  That's when I

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:15.350
dedicated myself
to becoming

00:00:15.916 --> 00:00:17.233
a rune hunter.

00:00:18.550 --> 00:00:23.150
As Farrow so kindly explained, runes are
very powerful and ancient inscriptions

00:00:23.150 --> 00:00:26.350
and can be inscribed on your items
to grant them more power.

00:00:26.900 --> 00:00:30.300
During the league, inscribing symbols
on traces will allow you to choose from

00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:33.983
several different crafting runes
that you can use to enhance your items.

00:00:34.633 --> 00:00:38.183
When a trace is found,
it will have a number of spaces ranging from two

00:00:38.733 --> 00:00:39.866
to seven.

00:00:39.866 --> 00:00:42.783
The more spaces you have,
the more powerful the encounter with traces will be, and the

00:00:42.783 --> 00:00:45.450
more options
you will have to choose from.

00:00:45.450 --> 00:00:47.333
Early in the game,
you may find yourself

00:00:47.333 --> 00:00:49.400
crafting simple damage or resistance runes

00:00:49.750 --> 00:00:51.116
that are available at a lower level

00:00:51.116 --> 00:00:52.616
than you would normally be able to
obtain them,

00:00:52.700 --> 00:00:54.433
providing a considerable power boost.

00:00:54.650 --> 00:00:56.516
But things quickly get more interesting.

00:00:57.250 --> 00:01:00.233
There are 22 runes to add
or modify Runic Safeguard,

00:01:00.483 --> 00:01:02.450
a new feature
that can protect against death.

00:01:03.033 --> 00:01:06.900
With these runes, you can add an
extra defensive layer or transform your Runic Safeguard

00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:10.150
into an offensive weapon
using Kalguuran runic abilities.

00:01:13.183 --> 00:01:16.600
There are also 13 runes that add
specific powers to weapon types,

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:19.833
such as this one, which gives grenades a chance to
explode a second time.

00:01:21.283 --> 00:01:24.566
Or this one, which gives you a new bonus
called Druidic Prowess

00:01:24.616 --> 00:01:26.200
when you completely stun enemies.

00:01:28.950 --> 00:01:29.850
In addition,

00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:32.850
there are 22 runes
designed to empower you at low levels,

00:01:32.850 --> 00:01:35.850
such as this one, which gives you
various elemental resistances,

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:38.683
or this one,
which gives you a lot of spirit.

00:01:38.683 --> 00:01:42.300
These runes are designed to be powerful,
but they lose value as you level up.

00:01:42.300 --> 00:01:45.300
They are great for
leveling up a second character in the league.  We

00:01:45.733 --> 00:01:47.933
also have six runes
that can be used to expand

00:01:47.933 --> 00:01:51.016
the list of modifiers used
during high-level creation.

00:01:51.600 --> 00:01:55.133
For example, you can fit
Katla's Darkness into a pair of gloves,

00:01:55.133 --> 00:01:58.516
and this will allow the creation
of several new rot modifiers

00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:00.650
that can be used in
degenerative damage archetypes.

00:02:01.216 --> 00:02:03.316
After fitting a rune of this type,

00:02:03.316 --> 00:02:06.416
use regular Exalted or Chaos Orbs to
try and create the new modifiers.

00:02:08.666 --> 00:02:10.583
There are also several runes that have

00:02:10.583 --> 00:02:13.900
unique and powerful effects on items,
but are permanently fixed in the socket,

00:02:14.066 --> 00:02:17.183
such as this one, which allows any item
to gain an additional suffix.

00:02:21.200 --> 00:02:23.516
Or this one,
which allows you to create a jewelry setting.

00:02:29.166 --> 00:02:30.400
Or this series of runes

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:33.566
that can convert any elemental modifier
from one element to another.

00:02:34.933 --> 00:02:37.700
There's even a rune
that can upgrade any other rune,

00:02:37.700 --> 00:02:39.750
allowing them to be upgraded
beyond the normal limit.

00:02:42.133 --> 00:02:45.133
The last one I want to show you
today is Aldur's Legacy.

00:02:45.433 --> 00:02:50.266
A special rune that can be fitted into any unique kalguurano or ezomyte item to destroy it

00:02:50.266 --> 00:02:53.233
and create a new rune that inherits some of the unique item's properties.

00:02:53.816 --> 00:02:54.983
For example,

00:02:54.983 --> 00:02:58.350
use this on a "Heavy March" rune
to create a "Heavy March Legacy" rune.

00:02:58.500 --> 00:02:59.950
Fit it into a pair of boots and,

00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:01.683
just like the unique item it came from,

00:03:01.683 --> 00:03:05.233
you'll deal 10% of the excess damage
to all enemies within a 2m radius.

00:03:05.983 --> 00:03:08.700
Or how about
"The Legacy of the Distorted Empyrean"?

00:03:08.700 --> 00:03:10.466
Destroy a "Wrought Empyrean Legacy"

00:03:10.466 --> 00:03:13.666
to add cold damage based
on your maximum mana to any weapon.

00:03:14.783 --> 00:03:17.900
With "Legacy of Aldur," you can create
over a hundred runes

00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:19.950
with all sorts of unique effects.

00:03:22.516 --> 00:03:25.116
Now you might be thinking: that
's a lot of new runes.  You're right

00:03:25.116 --> 00:03:26.350
.

00:03:26.350 --> 00:03:28.350
After all, it's the Runes of Aldur League.

00:03:28.350 --> 00:03:31.000
But we also didn't want the ancient runes to be
left behind.

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:32.700
A significant number of old, unused runes

00:03:32.700 --> 00:03:34.800
 
are also being upgraded,

00:03:34.800 --> 00:03:37.233
making this crafting system
significantly better.

00:03:37.566 --> 00:03:39.183
Explore all that runes have to offer

00:03:39.183 --> 00:03:42.883
in the Return of the Ancients update
on May 29th.  See you then!

